Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil.

In a small #pot, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Pat @Chicken Legs{16%ounce} dry with paper towels; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken, skin sides down; cook until skin is browned and crisp, ~{3-5%minutes}. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches.)

Remove from heat and flip chicken. (TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof or big enough, transfer chicken to a lightly oiled #baking sheet now.) Sprinkle chicken with @Herbes de Provence{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4). Roast on middle rack until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard bottom 1 inch from @Asparagus{6%ounce}. Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{9%ounce} into 1/4-inch rounds. Halve and peel @Shallot{1}; finely chop half (all for 4 servings). Pick @Parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

> For 4 servings, you may need to double the vegetable quantities.

Once water is boiling, add asparagus and carrots to #pot. Cook until asparagus is bright green and carrots are almost tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Drain and transfer veggies to a plate to cool. TIP: Make an ice bath and drop your veggies in immediately once they're drained so they stay bright and stop cooking.

Melt @Butter{3%tablespoon} (6 TBSP for 4 servings) in a second large #pan over medium-high heat. Cook, carefully swirling butter, until foamy and flecked with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}. TIP: If using a dark pan, scoop a small amount of butter in a metal spoon to check for those flecks.

Reduce heat to medium low and add chopped shallot; cook until softened ~{1-2%minutes}. Add half the @Brown Sugar{1%tablespoon} (all for 4) and half the @Red Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4); stir until the sugar has dissolved, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add blanched veggies and cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in half the parsley. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork.

Divide rice between bowls; top with chicken and veggies. Sprinkle with remaining parsley and serve.